      <section eId="sec_15_16_28">
        <num>15-16-28</num>
        <content>
          <p>In any county there may be created by local Act of the General Assembly a merit board to hear and decide appeals from disciplinary actions against deputies and other employees of the sheriff of the county; provided, however, that no such merit board or appeals procedure shall become effective until approved and adopted by the sheriff.</p>
